BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 3.256945 Tw (There is a widespread belief that failures in modern systems are caused by complexity \227 artificial) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.517107 Tw (intelligence, machine learning, automation, and advanced computation. The assumption is that simpler) Tj T* 0 Tw 3.025783 Tw (systems, operating on deterministic rules with predictable outputs, are inherently safer. This belief is) Tj T* 0 Tw .411199 Tw (incorrect, and its persistence is one of the most significant barriers to effective governance of modern digital) Tj T* 0 Tw (infrastructure.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 475.111 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .261275 Tw (Failure does not begin with intelligence. Failure begins with authority. A system does not need to be capable) Tj T* 0 Tw .066273 Tw (of learning, adapting, or reasoning in order to produce harm at scale. It needs only one property: the ability to) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.830079 Tw (act. And when that action occurs without authority validation at the moment of execution, the failure) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.041066 Tw (mechanism is identical regardless of whether the system is powered by a neural network or a set of fixed) Tj T* 0 Tw (conditional rules written in the 1990s.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 383.7724 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .016949 Tw (Simple systems fail for the same reason complex systems fail: they act without verifying whether they should.) Tj T* 0 Tw .993514 Tw (A banking system transferring funds, a government system issuing penalties, a payment gateway blocking) Tj T* 0 Tw .120679 Tw (access, or an identity system denying authentication \227 none of these require artificial intelligence to produce) Tj T* 0 Tw .758069 Tw (harm. They require only one condition: they must act. And when they act without authority validation at the) Tj T* 0 Tw (moment of execution, they fail.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 276.4339 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 86.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .472812 Tw (Systems are trusted because they appear predictable. They are trusted because they follow rules. But rules) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.491845 Tw (are not authority. Rules define what can happen. Authority defines what should happen. When a system) Tj T* 0 Tw .547014 Tw (follows rules without evaluating authority, it produces outcomes that are technically correct but operationally) Tj T* 0 Tw -0.041066 Tw (wrong. This is the most dangerous type of failure \227 failure that looks correct. It does not trigger alerts. It does) Tj T* 0 Tw .367045 Tw (not produce visible errors. It produces outcomes that the system was designed to produce, under conditions) Tj T* 0 Tw (that no longer justify them.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
