BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .966179 Tw (Non-AI systems are trusted not because they are correct, but because they are consistent. Consistency is) Tj T* 0 Tw .388128 Tw (mistaken for reliability. A system that produces the same result repeatedly is assumed to be correct \227 even) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.387918 Tw (when that result is wrong. This assumption is reinforced by the stability of the system's behaviour, which) Tj T* 0 Tw .508912 Tw (signals reliability rather than correctness, and which persists because the failure pattern is embedded in the) Tj T* 0 Tw (design rather than arising from a defect.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 339.7953 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 1.032975 Tw (This creates a dangerous condition: failure becomes predictable \227 and therefore acceptable. When users) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.74301 Tw (can reliably anticipate how a system will fail, they adapt to that failure rather than demanding that it be) Tj T* 0 Tw .683712 Tw (corrected. They expect false declines and plan for them. They accept incorrect blocks and navigate around) Tj T* 0 Tw -0.049431 Tw (them. They experience repeated loss of access and learn the procedure for regaining it. They absorb the cost) Tj T* 0 Tw (of the system's incorrect operation as a feature of how the system works.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 264.4567 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 54.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .261275 Tw (The system is not fixed. The user adapts. Over time, the adapted behaviour of users becomes evidence that) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.671079 Tw (the system is working \227 because users are successfully interacting with it, even though that interaction) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.724283 Tw (includes routine workarounds for routine failures. The failures become invisible because they have been) Tj T* 0 Tw (absorbed into normal user behaviour.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
