.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 86.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .245543 Tw (A system either validates authority at execution or it operates on assumption. There is no intermediate state.) Tj T* 0 Tw .199246 Tw (A system that validates authority in some cases but not others does not have partial authority governance \227) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.650773 Tw (it has gaps in its governance, and those gaps are the points at which failure occurs. The measure of a) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.332927 Tw (governance model is not how many cases it covers but whether it covers the cases that matter. And the) Tj T* 0 Tw .233773 Tw (cases that matter are the ones in which authority is most likely to have changed between the point of access) Tj T* 0 Tw (and the point of action.) Tj T* ET
