BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .334112 Tw (A deterministic system can fail with perfect consistency. It can apply incorrect conditions without deviation. It) Tj T* 0 Tw .474079 Tw (can enforce invalid outcomes with absolute reliability. In fact, the absence of variability makes these failures) Tj T* 0 Tw -0.050548 Tw (more dangerous, not less, because they are harder to detect. They do not appear as anomalies. They appear) Tj T* 0 Tw .409418 Tw (as stable operation \227 the predictable, repeatable behaviour of a system doing exactly what it was designed) Tj T* 0 Tw (to do, under conditions its design never anticipated.) Tj T* ET
