BT 1 0 0 1 0 54.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 3.078979 Tw (A system that always produces the same incorrect outcome is more dangerous than a system that) Tj T* 0 Tw .631052 Tw (occasionally produces visible errors. The latter draws attention. The former normalises failure. Users adapt.) Tj T* 0 Tw -0.105795 Tw (Institutions accept it. Regulators treat it as the cost of scale. And the failure continues \227 embedded in design,) Tj T* 0 Tw (executed consistently, invisible behind its own predictability.) Tj T* ET
