BT 1 0 0 1 0 54.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 1.037011 Tw (The presence of artificial intelligence does not introduce the authority problem. It reveals it. It exposes the) Tj T* 0 Tw .419422 Tw (same structural flaw that has always existed in simpler systems \227 now at greater speed, greater scale, and) Tj T* 0 Tw .825579 Tw (greater consequence. The conclusion is unavoidable: if a system can act without validating authority, it will) Tj T* 0 Tw (produce unauthorised outcomes \227 regardless of whether it is intelligent or not.) Tj T* ET
