BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 1.248012 Tw (All modern systems are designed to continue operating. Persistence is treated as a desirable property \227) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.847789 Tw (systems should remain available, processes should not interrupt, transactions should complete, services) Tj T* 0 Tw .109682 Tw (should remain responsive. These are legitimate operational objectives. The problem arises when persistence) Tj T* 0 Tw .540636 Tw (becomes the default behaviour in the absence of authority validation, because it means that every failure of) Tj T* 0 Tw (authority governance is met with the same response: continuation.) Tj T* ET
Q
