BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .356275 Tw (Control is often misunderstood as the ability to configure a system, to assign permissions, or to define rules.) Tj T* 0 Tw .639793 Tw (These capabilities create the appearance of control \227 they demonstrate that the system can be shaped by) Tj T* 0 Tw .244949 Tw (human decisions \227 but they do not determine whether control exists at the moment of action. Configuration,) Tj T* 0 Tw .508279 Tw (permission assignment, and rule definition all occur before execution. They are acts of preparation, not acts) Tj T* 0 Tw (of control.) Tj T* ET
