BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL -0.106294 Tw (Modern systems do not operate in isolation. They are interconnected, integrated, and interdependent. Actions) Tj T* 0 Tw .385893 Tw (taken in one system propagate into others. A decision made in a payment system affects a banking system.) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.53398 Tw (A change in an identity system affects access control systems. A classification in a fraud system affects) Tj T* 0 Tw .791562 Tw (transaction systems. This interconnection creates an amplification effect that transforms individual authority) Tj T* 0 Tw (failures into systemic ones.) Tj T* ET
