BT 1 0 0 1 0 54.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL .292569 Tw (There is a persistent belief that system failures represent defects \227 that something has gone wrong, that an) Tj T* 0 Tw -0.018676 Tw (error has occurred, that the system has deviated from expected behaviour. This belief leads to the conclusion) Tj T* 0 Tw .177773 Tw (that failures can be addressed by finding and fixing the defect. It is a comforting belief because it implies that) Tj T* 0 Tw (the system, once fixed, will be correct. It is also incorrect.) Tj T* ET
