.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 86.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 1.565312 Tw (Most failures in non-AI systems occur because the system is operating exactly as designed. The design) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.520399 Tw (assumes that authentication is sufficient, that permissions persist, that conditions remain stable, and that) Tj T* 0 Tw .635579 Tw (prior approval remains valid. These assumptions are embedded in the system's logic. The system does not) Tj T* 0 Tw .479775 Tw (question them because it was never designed to do so. When a system blocks a legitimate user, processes) Tj T* 0 Tw .418305 Tw (an incorrect transaction, or enforces an invalid decision, it is not malfunctioning. It is applying its rules under) Tj T* 0 Tw (assumptions that no longer reflect reality.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 68.3622 249.4567 cm
q
.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 86.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 1.652273 Tw (The failure is not in execution. It is in design. And this distinction is critical, because it changes what is) Tj T* 0 Tw .670484 Tw (required to address it. A system that fails due to a defect can be fixed \227 the defect is identified, corrected,) Tj T* 0 Tw .328009 Tw (and the system returns to correct operation. A system that fails due to its design cannot be fixed in this way.) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.070855 Tw (Fixing a defect does not address the structural assumption that produced the failure. The failure will recur) Tj T* 0 Tw .353906 Tw (under the same conditions, because those conditions expose the design assumption rather than triggering a) Tj T* 0 Tw (defect.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
